<paragraph id="8BB736F2215FFFF2FF221BBEFE1DFF31" blockId="13.[151,857,151,213]" box="[151,387,187,213]" pageId="13" pageNumber="224">
(
<figureCitation id="13332A77215FFFF2FF2A1BBEFEB5FF31" box="[159,299,187,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1866,1890]" captionTargetBox="[171,1412,191,1824]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[171,1416,181,1841]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Grammedessa. A–B: G. hamata comb.n. A: Dorsal view. B: Ventral view. C–D: G. nigricava sp.n. C: Dorsal view. D: Ventral view. E–F: G. longispina sp.n. E: Dorsal view. F: Ventral view. G–H: G. fundicava sp.n. G: Dorsal view. H: Ventral view. I–J: G. graciligramma sp.n. I: Dorsal view. J: Ventral view. K–L: G. stichtocephala sp.n. K: Dorsal view. L: Ventral view. M–N: G. acalyptoprocta sp.n. M: Dorsal view. N: Ventral view. Scale = 10 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500667" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500667/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="224">Figs. 1M–N</figureCitation>
; 
<figureCitation id="13332A77215FFFF2FE821BBEFEE5FF31" box="[311,379,187,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1956,1980]" captionTargetBox="[151,1423,576,1915]" captionTargetId="figure-151@13.[151,1435,561,1932]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 8. Male genitalia of G. acalyptoprocta sp.n. A: Pygophore in dorsal view. B: Pygophore in ventral view. C: Pygophore in posterior view. Scale = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500695" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500695/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="224">8A–C</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3126579215FFFF2FF221A06FCE9FDFD" pageId="13" pageNumber="224" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BB736F2215FFFF2FF221A06FCE9FDFD" blockId="13.[151,1437,259,537]" pageId="13" pageNumber="224">
<emphasis id="B97CEAE0215FFFF2FF221A06FE8FFEF9" bold="true" box="[151,273,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="224">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Length 
<quantity id="4CF09B17215FFFF2FEDB1A06FE4BFEFA" box="[366,469,259,286]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.97" pageId="13" pageNumber="224" unit="mm" value="19.7">19.7 mm</quantity>
. Width 
<quantity id="4CF09B17215FFFF2FD9F1A06FDE2FEFA" box="[554,636,259,286]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3" pageId="13" pageNumber="224" unit="mm" value="13.0">13 mm</quantity>
. Body green with tiny yellow speckles; beneath abdomen with a medial yellow large spot. Densely punctured, punctures brown (
<figureCitation id="13332A77215FFFF2FC871A22FC0AFEA5" box="[818,916,295,321]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1866,1890]" captionTargetBox="[171,1412,191,1824]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[171,1416,181,1841]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Grammedessa. A–B: G. hamata comb.n. A: Dorsal view. B: Ventral view. C–D: G. nigricava sp.n. C: Dorsal view. D: Ventral view. E–F: G. longispina sp.n. E: Dorsal view. F: Ventral view. G–H: G. fundicava sp.n. G: Dorsal view. H: Ventral view. I–J: G. graciligramma sp.n. I: Dorsal view. J: Ventral view. K–L: G. stichtocephala sp.n. K: Dorsal view. L: Ventral view. M–N: G. acalyptoprocta sp.n. M: Dorsal view. N: Ventral view. Scale = 10 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500667" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500667/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="224">Fig. 1M</figureCitation>
). Bucculae punctured, some punctures dark. Humeral angles projection developed, dentiform, ventrally punctured (
<figureCitation id="13332A77215FFFF2FC101A4EFC63FE81" box="[933,1021,331,357]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1866,1890]" captionTargetBox="[171,1412,191,1824]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[171,1416,181,1841]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Grammedessa. A–B: G. hamata comb.n. A: Dorsal view. B: Ventral view. C–D: G. nigricava sp.n. C: Dorsal view. D: Ventral view. E–F: G. longispina sp.n. E: Dorsal view. F: Ventral view. G–H: G. fundicava sp.n. G: Dorsal view. H: Ventral view. I–J: G. graciligramma sp.n. I: Dorsal view. J: Ventral view. K–L: G. stichtocephala sp.n. K: Dorsal view. L: Ventral view. M–N: G. acalyptoprocta sp.n. M: Dorsal view. N: Ventral view. Scale = 10 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500667" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500667/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="224">Fig. 1N</figureCitation>
). Hypocostal ridge green with yellow speckles and brown punctures. Beneath thorax densely punctured, punctures coarse and brown; abdomen shagreen and sparsely punctured, punctures small and concolorous with the background (
<figureCitation id="13332A77215FFFF2FB9C1A96FB1AFE49" box="[1065,1156,403,429]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1866,1890]" captionTargetBox="[171,1412,191,1824]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[171,1416,181,1841]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Grammedessa. A–B: G. hamata comb.n. A: Dorsal view. B: Ventral view. C–D: G. nigricava sp.n. C: Dorsal view. D: Ventral view. E–F: G. longispina sp.n. E: Dorsal view. F: Ventral view. G–H: G. fundicava sp.n. G: Dorsal view. H: Ventral view. I–J: G. graciligramma sp.n. I: Dorsal view. J: Ventral view. K–L: G. stichtocephala sp.n. K: Dorsal view. L: Ventral view. M–N: G. acalyptoprocta sp.n. M: Dorsal view. N: Ventral view. Scale = 10 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500667" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500667/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="224">Fig. 1N</figureCitation>
). First three and base of fourth antennal segments with dense, small dark spots. Legs with dense dark spots. Dorsal rim of pygophore with small rounded projections above superior processes of the genital cup (
<figureCitation id="13332A77215FFFF2FC081ADEFB86FE11" box="[957,1048,475,501]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1956,1980]" captionTargetBox="[151,1423,576,1915]" captionTargetId="figure-151@13.[151,1435,561,1932]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 8. Male genitalia of G. acalyptoprocta sp.n. A: Pygophore in dorsal view. B: Pygophore in ventral view. C: Pygophore in posterior view. Scale = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500695" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500695/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="224">Fig. 8A</figureCitation>
); ventral rim more excavated than dorsal rim leaving anal opening completely exposed (
<figureCitation id="13332A77215FFFF2FD5A1AFAFCF5FDFD" box="[751,875,511,537]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1956,1980]" captionTargetBox="[151,1423,576,1915]" captionTargetId="figure-151@13.[151,1435,561,1932]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 8. Male genitalia of G. acalyptoprocta sp.n. A: Pygophore in dorsal view. B: Pygophore in ventral view. C: Pygophore in posterior view. Scale = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500695" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500695/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="224">Fig. 8A–B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption id="DF77667A215FFFF2FF221CA1FE7FF83B" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500695" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6500695" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500695/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="224" startId="13.[151,250,1956,1980]" targetBox="[151,1423,576,1915]" targetPageId="13">
<paragraph id="8BB736F2215FFFF2FF221CA1FE7FF83B" blockId="13.[151,1436,1956,2016]" pageId="13" pageNumber="224">
<emphasis id="B97CEAE0215FFFF2FF221CA1FE8CF858" bold="true" box="[151,274,1956,1980]" pageId="13" pageNumber="224">FIGURE 8.</emphasis>
Male genitalia of 
<taxonomicName id="4C084D71215FFFF2FE721CA1FDE3F858" authority="Silva &amp; Fernandes, 2022" authorityName="Da Silva &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2022" box="[455,637,1956,1980]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Grammedessa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="224" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="acalyptoprocta" status="sp.n.">
<emphasis id="B97CEAE0215FFFF2FE721CA1FDE3F858" box="[455,637,1956,1980]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="224">G. acalyptoprocta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B97CEAE0215FFFF2FD361CA1FD2BF858" bold="true" box="[643,693,1956,1980]" pageId="13" pageNumber="224">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A24F579B215FFFF2FD361CA1FD2BF858" box="[643,693,1956,1980]" pageId="13" pageNumber="224" rank="species">sp.n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
A: Pygophore in dorsal view. B: Pygophore in ventral view. C: Pygophore in posterior view. Scale = 1 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<subSubSection id="C3126579215CFFF1FF721B92FDFDFD4D" pageId="14" pageNumber="225" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BB736F2215CFFF1FF721B92FD76FE81" blockId="14.[151,1437,150,969]" pageId="14" pageNumber="225">
<emphasis id="B97CEAE0215CFFF1FF721B92FECAFF55" bold="true" box="[199,340,151,177]" pageId="14" pageNumber="225">
<emphasis id="B97CEAE0215CFFF1FF721B92FED3FF55" bold="true" box="[199,333,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="225">Description</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Head wider than long (1.5 times). Thorax: pronotum wider than long (3 times); cicatrices with a row of concolorous punctures, delimited by groove and punctures. Evaporatorium dull, whitish, not punctured, shagreen; lateral areas coarsely punctured, not spotted, half-moon shaped (
<figureCitation id="13332A77215CFFF1FC581BDAFBD9FF1D" box="[1005,1095,223,249]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1866,1890]" captionTargetBox="[171,1412,191,1824]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[171,1416,181,1841]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Grammedessa. A–B: G. hamata comb.n. A: Dorsal view. B: Ventral view. C–D: G. nigricava sp.n. C: Dorsal view. D: Ventral view. E–F: G. longispina sp.n. E: Dorsal view. F: Ventral view. G–H: G. fundicava sp.n. G: Dorsal view. H: Ventral view. I–J: G. graciligramma sp.n. I: Dorsal view. J: Ventral view. K–L: G. stichtocephala sp.n. K: Dorsal view. L: Ventral view. M–N: G. acalyptoprocta sp.n. M: Dorsal view. N: Ventral view. Scale = 10 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500667" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500667/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="225">Fig. 1N</figureCitation>
). Metasternal process yellow; anterior bifurcation with arms abruptly acuminate; not spotted (
<figureCitation id="13332A77215CFFF1FCF81A06FC3AFEF9" box="[845,932,259,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1866,1890]" captionTargetBox="[171,1412,191,1824]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[171,1416,181,1841]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Grammedessa. A–B: G. hamata comb.n. A: Dorsal view. B: Ventral view. C–D: G. nigricava sp.n. C: Dorsal view. D: Ventral view. E–F: G. longispina sp.n. E: Dorsal view. F: Ventral view. G–H: G. fundicava sp.n. G: Dorsal view. H: Ventral view. I–J: G. graciligramma sp.n. I: Dorsal view. J: Ventral view. K–L: G. stichtocephala sp.n. K: Dorsal view. L: Ventral view. M–N: G. acalyptoprocta sp.n. M: Dorsal view. N: Ventral view. Scale = 10 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500667" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500667/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="225">Fig. 1N</figureCitation>
). Abdomen: connexivum densely punctuated, punctures green; segments III–VI medially with a callus; segment VII with distal margin and a few distal punctures black. Beneath both trichobothria lateral to spiracles.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB736F2215CFFF1FF721A6BFDFDFD4D" blockId="14.[151,1437,150,969]" pageId="14" pageNumber="225">
<emphasis id="B97CEAE0215CFFF1FF721A6BFE9CFE6D" bold="true" box="[199,258,366,393]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="225">Male</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="13332A77215CFFF1FEA61A6AFE0EFE6D" box="[275,400,367,393]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1956,1980]" captionTargetBox="[151,1423,576,1915]" captionTargetId="figure-151@13.[151,1435,561,1932]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 8. Male genitalia of G. acalyptoprocta sp.n. A: Pygophore in dorsal view. B: Pygophore in ventral view. C: Pygophore in posterior view. Scale = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500695" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500695/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="225">Fig. 8A–C</figureCitation>
). Pygophore yellow, trapezoidal (1.1 times). Dorsal rim sinuous and slightly projected over the genital cup (
<figureCitation id="13332A77215CFFF1FEFD1A96FE3EFE49" box="[328,416,403,429]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1956,1980]" captionTargetBox="[151,1423,576,1915]" captionTargetId="figure-151@13.[151,1435,561,1932]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 8. Male genitalia of G. acalyptoprocta sp.n. A: Pygophore in dorsal view. B: Pygophore in ventral view. C: Pygophore in posterior view. Scale = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500695" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500695/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="225">Fig. 8A</figureCitation>
). Posterolateral angles strongly developed, shallowly concave; inner part with a large brown spot and outlined by a narrow dark stripe (
<figureCitation id="13332A77215CFFF1FD321AB2FC93FE35" box="[647,781,439,465]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1956,1980]" captionTargetBox="[151,1423,576,1915]" captionTargetId="figure-151@13.[151,1435,561,1932]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 8. Male genitalia of G. acalyptoprocta sp.n. A: Pygophore in dorsal view. B: Pygophore in ventral view. C: Pygophore in posterior view. Scale = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500695" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500695/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="225">Fig. 8 A–B</figureCitation>
). Superior processes of the genital cup elliptic, projected dorsally passing dorsal rim (
<figureCitation id="13332A77215CFFF1FE6F1ADEFDADFE11" box="[474,563,475,501]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1956,1980]" captionTargetBox="[151,1423,576,1915]" captionTargetId="figure-151@13.[151,1435,561,1932]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 8. Male genitalia of G. acalyptoprocta sp.n. A: Pygophore in dorsal view. B: Pygophore in ventral view. C: Pygophore in posterior view. Scale = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500695" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500695/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="225">Fig. 8C</figureCitation>
). Parameres posteriorly carinated; anterior lobe developed and subtriangular; posterior lobe short and triangular (
<figureCitation id="13332A77215CFFF1FD901AFAFDE3FDFD" box="[549,637,511,537]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1956,1980]" captionTargetBox="[151,1423,576,1915]" captionTargetId="figure-151@13.[151,1435,561,1932]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 8. Male genitalia of G. acalyptoprocta sp.n. A: Pygophore in dorsal view. B: Pygophore in ventral view. C: Pygophore in posterior view. Scale = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500695" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500695/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="225">Fig. 8C</figureCitation>
). Proctiger brown, elongated (1.3 times); medial carina of the posterior surface bifurcated on distal half (
<figureCitation id="13332A77215CFFF1FDAC1926FD06FDD9" box="[537,664,547,573]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1956,1980]" captionTargetBox="[151,1423,576,1915]" captionTargetId="figure-151@13.[151,1435,561,1932]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 8. Male genitalia of G. acalyptoprocta sp.n. A: Pygophore in dorsal view. B: Pygophore in ventral view. C: Pygophore in posterior view. Scale = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500695" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500695/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="225">Fig. 8A–B</figureCitation>
). Ventral rim widely opened, strongly excavated, more than dorsal rim (
<figureCitation id="13332A77215CFFF1FF7A1942FEB5FD85" box="[207,299,583,609]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1956,1980]" captionTargetBox="[151,1423,576,1915]" captionTargetId="figure-151@13.[151,1435,561,1932]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 8. Male genitalia of G. acalyptoprocta sp.n. A: Pygophore in dorsal view. B: Pygophore in ventral view. C: Pygophore in posterior view. Scale = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500695" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500695/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="225">Fig. 8A</figureCitation>
); expansions developed, tumid, close to posterolateral angles (
<figureCitation id="13332A77215CFFF1FC431942FBEAFD85" box="[1014,1140,583,609]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1956,1980]" captionTargetBox="[151,1423,576,1915]" captionTargetId="figure-151@13.[151,1435,561,1932]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 8. Male genitalia of G. acalyptoprocta sp.n. A: Pygophore in dorsal view. B: Pygophore in ventral view. C: Pygophore in posterior view. Scale = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500695" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500695/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="225">Fig. 8A–C</figureCitation>
); curved inwards, densely punctured, black.Ventral surface densely punctured close to the ventral rim, punctures of different sizes, concolorous to black, a few on brown spots (
<figureCitation id="13332A77215CFFF1FE48198AFDCBFD4D" box="[509,597,655,681]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1956,1980]" captionTargetBox="[151,1423,576,1915]" captionTargetId="figure-151@13.[151,1435,561,1932]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 8. Male genitalia of G. acalyptoprocta sp.n. A: Pygophore in dorsal view. B: Pygophore in ventral view. C: Pygophore in posterior view. Scale = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500695" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500695/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="225">Fig. 8B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3126579215CFFF1FF7219B7FC96FD15" pageId="14" pageNumber="225" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BB736F2215CFFF1FF7219B7FC96FD15" blockId="14.[151,1437,150,969]" pageId="14" pageNumber="225">
<emphasis id="B97CEAE0215CFFF1FF7219B7FED7FD29" bold="true" box="[199,329,690,717]" pageId="14" pageNumber="225">
<emphasis id="B97CEAE0215CFFF1FF7219B7FEDCFD29" bold="true" box="[199,322,690,717]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="225">Etymology</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Named by its exposed anal opening caused by an extremely excavated ventral rim. From the Greek. 
<emphasis id="B97CEAE0215CFFF1FF2219D2FE9BFD15" box="[151,261,727,753]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="225">Akalyptos</emphasis>
(uncovered) and 
<emphasis id="B97CEAE0215CFFF1FE7F19D2FDBEFD15" box="[458,544,727,753]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="225">Proktos</emphasis>
(anus, hinder parts).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3126579215CFFF1FF7219FEFCFFFC42" pageId="14" pageNumber="225" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BB736F2215CFFF1FF7219FEFC9FFCB9" blockId="14.[151,1437,150,969]" pageId="14" pageNumber="225">
<emphasis id="B97CEAE0215CFFF1FF7219FEFED7FCF1" bold="true" box="[199,329,763,789]" pageId="14" pageNumber="225">
<emphasis id="B97CEAE0215CFFF1FF7219FEFEDCFCF1" bold="true" box="[199,322,763,789]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="225">Comments</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Resemble 
<taxonomicName id="4C084D71215CFFF1FE7B19FEFD3FFCF1" authorityName="Correia &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2016" box="[462,673,763,789]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Grammedessa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="225" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brunneotarsata">
<emphasis id="B97CEAE0215CFFF1FE7B19FEFD3FFCF1" box="[462,673,763,789]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="225">G. brunneotarsata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by its non-spotted tegument and shape of parameres; but can be differentiated by its spotted outer faces of the bucculae, trichobothria lateral to spiracles, and the upper half of posterior face of pygophore with keel medially sulcate.
</paragraph>
